<br>
How do these sound for a “Body-Baton” relay race? <br>
<br>
There should be an entrance fee for each team that wishes to participate. This “fee” will be the purse money that the winning team will get. Say 100pp per team. <br>
<br>
One of the Council can hold the entrant fees then dash to Kelethin to award the winners. <br>
<br>
1. Each team will have three Bards and ONE Warrior Class runner. <br>
<br>
2. Bards should range from level 5-15 the Warrior should be level 5-15. <br>
<br>
3. No SOW or HEAL type spells can be cast on ANY participant. Teleporting will not be allowed either. Any team caught cheating will be automatically disqualified and entrance fee forfeited. <br>
<br>
4. Because there are 3 Bards, there will only be 3 relay points. <br>
<br>
5. Each relay point should have at least ONE referee representative of each participating guild or team. <br>
<br>
6. Helping another team in trouble IS NOT required. That should be a moral call on the Bard and the Warrior runner that witness a team in distress. <br>
<br>
Anybody else have more thoughts? Do we want to do something like this? <br>
